content:
The Integration Procedure Action runs a subordinate Integration Procedure. To specify that the subordinate Integration Procedure runs asynchronously, select Remote Options and enter useFuture: as a key and true as its value. You can also pass in data as key/value pairs using the Additional Input property.

Integration Procedure Actions have unique properties, including the ability to run a subordinate procedure with asynchronous execution. A workflow example involves transforming a list of paired values into keys and values using parent and child Integration Procedures.
title: Integration Procedure Actions in OmniStudio
